(On the above date and time, Officer Halvorsen and Officer Ocampo responded to a) Tj
T*
(report of a disturbance at the 7-Eleven at 2100 Welton Street. Upon arrival officers) Tj
T*
(observed a male subject, later identified as Wendell Vanmeter, pacing in the parking) Tj
T*
(lot and shouting at no one visible. The store clerk, Bashir Kahlani, stated that the) Tj
T*
(subject had entered the store approximately ten minutes earlier, grabbed a store) Tj
T*
(employee by the shirt, and accused the employee of "broadcasting from the fluorescent) Tj
T*
(lights." The clerk stated the subject did not steal anything and appeared to be in) Tj
T*
("some kind of episode.") Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Officers approached the subject with verbal commands. The subject initially complied) Tj
T*
(and provided his name as Wendell Vanmeter. When officers attempted to detain the) Tj
T*
(subject for questioning the subject pulled away, shouted "you're one of them too,") Tj
T*
(and struck Officer Halvorsen once in the chest with a closed fist. Officer Ocampo) Tj
T*
(assisted in the takedown. The subject was placed in handcuffs without further) Tj
T*
(incident.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
